    &lt;Title&gt;Long Day in day case unit&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I would like to know why my husband was asked to arrive for his test under anaesthetic at 7.30 in the morning when it was obvious as indicated by the consultant that the procedure would be in the afternoon. His procedure took place at 5.00pm so he had spent all those hours with no food or fluids in a chair in a waiting room.  I appreciate the hospital prioritises but on this occasion he had his procedure day changed twice and a 14hr day.
He last had this procedure done in 2014 in very different circumstances. 
He found the staff great but the organisation seems poor.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
